{% extends "base.jinja" %}

{% block content %}
    <div class="summary-container">
        <div class="key-insights">
            <h2>Top 3 Recommendations</h2>
            <ol>
                <li><strong>Enhanced Membership Incentives:</strong> Introduce ride credit bundles and loyalty rewards to increase engagement, particularly among frequent riders.
                    <ul>
                        <li>Members ride 62% more often than casual users, and offering loyalty rewards for frequent riders will boost retention.</li>
                        <li>Incentivize existing members to refer casual users with rewards for successful conversions.</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><strong>Location-Centric Engagement:</strong> Focus marketing efforts on stations with a high number of casual users, particularly <strong>Streeter Dr & Grand Ave</strong>, during peak cycling times, such as Saturdays from 4 PM to 6 PM in summer. Collaborate with nearby businesses to offer exclusive member discounts.
                    <ul>
                        <li>Targeted marketing in these key locations ensures engagement where casual ridership is highest.</li>
                        <li>Partnerships with local businesses provide immediate value to members, fostering community engagement.</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><strong>Targeted Digital Media Campaigns:</strong> Launch a comprehensive social media campaign that highlights member benefits through engaging content and user-generated testimonials.
                    <ul>
                        <li>Leverage local influencers to promote membership through authentic experiences, creating relatable narratives that resonate with casual riders.</li>
                        <li>Incorporate limited-time membership discounts in digital ads to incentivize immediate sign-ups, enhancing urgency and appeal.</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </div>

        <h2>Additional Strategies for Membership Growth</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Feedback Mechanisms:</strong> Gather insights through user surveys to refine membership offerings and better address rider needs. Use data from these insights to evolve membership benefits.</li>
            <li><strong>Infrastructure Investment:</strong> Advocate for improved bike lanes and dedicated cycling paths to enhance safety and accessibility. Investing in infrastructure will encourage more users to bike and join the membership.</li>
            <li><strong>Bike Safety Initiatives:</strong> Implement safety programs that include rider education, safety gear discounts, and partnerships with local law enforcement to promote safe riding practices. Prioritizing bike safety will build trust and attract more users to become members.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
{% endblock %}
